An ANN is a computational framework inspired by the neural architecture of the human brain. It consists of interconnected units known as neurons, which are organized into various layers such as an input layer, several hidden layers, and an output layer. Each neuron in these layers is linked through weights that influence the signals transmitted between neurons. ANNs are employed in machine learning for their ability to adaptively learn from data, enabling them to perform tasks such as pattern recognition, classification, and regression15. For an ANN with two hidden layers, the final output \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
