				\begin{document}$$\:{X}_{4}$$\end{document} are the input parameters. The hyperparameter settings of the GA under MATLAB software are summarized in Table 6. The population consists of 25 individuals with a double vector representation, and the algorithm runs for a maximum of 25 generations. A uniform creation function initializes the population, with rank scaling and roulette selection enhancing diversity and selection pressure. One elite individual is carried over to the next generation. The mutation function uses adaptive feasible strategies, applied to 50% of the population, while a two-point crossover method is employed with a crossover fraction of 50%. Migration occurs forward at 10% intervals, with 90% of the population migrating. A penalty-based approach addresses nonlinear constraints, and the cost limit is set to zero.
